OL,3,CTripling of physician associates
OL,4,Cleaves doctors 'concerned and
OL,5,Cfrightened'
OL,7,FNHS Wales says physician associates
OL,8,F(PAs) are clinically trained,
OL,9,Fgeneralist healthcare professionals,
OL,10,Fwho work alongside doctors and provide
OL,11,Fmedical care as an integral part of
OL,12,Fthe multidisciplinary team.
OL,14,FBut the BMA says patients who come to
OL,15,Fhospital do not always know whether
OL,16,Fthey are speaking to a qualified
OL,17,Fdoctor when they are seeking advice or
OL,18,Fdiagnosis, and the confusion can lead
OL,19,Fto patients not getting the correct
OL,20,Fcare.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/21
