OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F466A1731092484
OL,3,CTripling of physician associates
OL,4,Cleaves doctors 'concerned and
OL,5,Cfrightened'
OL,7,F"Simply put, the two year training
OL,8,Fdoes not equate them at all with what
OL,9,Fa doctor has to go through in order to
OL,10,Fqualify to call themselves a doctor.
OL,11,FThey are not doctors associates, they
OL,12,Fare doctors assistants".
OL,14,FIn response to our investigation, a
OL,15,FWelsh Government spokesperson said:
OL,16,F"Physician associates play an
OL,17,Fimportant role in the NHS in Wales,
OL,18,Fbut we are clear they are there to
OL,19,Fsupport the work of doctors, not
OL,20,Freplace them.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/21
