OL,3,CTripling of physician associates
OL,4,Cleaves doctors 'concerned and
OL,5,Cfrightened'
OL,7,F"On top of that, there is an
OL,8,Fassumption that whoever is working
OL,9,Fwith that physician associate as a
OL,10,Fdoctor has assumed the responsibility
OL,11,Fof supervising that physician
OL,12,Fassociate so if they make a clinical
OL,13,Ferror then the blame lies with the
OL,14,Fdoctor who allowed that clinical error
OL,15,Fto take place, and that is very
OL,16,Fconcerning for doctors.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/21
